[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1387},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fwebpack\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F09\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fwebpack\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F09\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fwebpack\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F09\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fwebpack\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F09\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev\u002F":1363,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fwebpack\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F09\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev\u002F":1372},"\u002Fwebpack\u002F20190609\u002F3910344198\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1348,"date":1349,"description":19,"extension":1350,"lang":1351,"meta":1352,"navigation":331,"path":1353,"readingMinutes":1354,"seo":1355,"standalone":1356,"stem":1357,"tags":1358,"tldr":1360,"updated":1360,"url":1361,"__hash__":1362},"content\u002Fen\u002FWebpack\u002Fwebpack-learning-ep-11-prod-dev.md","EP 11 - Learning Webpack the Hard Way: prod vs dev","4198391034",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1336},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,37,40,43,56,63,78,158,164,171,176,183,188,198,204,207,213,219,223,234,237,265,275,279,411,414,658,662,1263,1266,1312,1316,1325,1332],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Webpack usually has two build modes: prod and dev. Let me log how to set them up.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"what-are-prod-and-dev","What are prod and dev?",[17,25,26],{},"Quick decoder first:",[28,29,30,34],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"prod: production — usually compresses and optimizes files",[31,35,36],{},"dev: development — just compiles, no optimization",[17,38,39],{},"What's the difference? When you're still building locally, you're testing constantly. If every test build does full minification and optimization, that wastes a ton of resources. For a big project, you might find your computer frozen while it churns. So we split prod vs dev.",[12,41,42],{"id":42},"webpack4",[17,44,45,46,50,51,55],{},"In webpack4, ",[47,48,49],"strong",{},"the default compile mode is prod",". For example, just running ",[52,53,54],"code",{},"webpack"," on its own will minify and optimize:",[17,57,58],{},[59,60],"img",{"alt":61,"src":62},"Default build","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcPgIDN1.png",[17,64,65,66,69,70,73,74,77],{},"How do we avoid that? Easiest path: add custom scripts to ",[52,67,68],{},"package.json"," (I renamed my ",[52,71,72],{},"start"," to ",[52,75,76],{},"server","):",[79,80,85],"pre",{"className":81,"code":82,"language":83,"meta":84,"style":84},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\"scripts\": {\n  \"server\": \"webpack-dev-server --config webpack.config.js\",\n  \"dev\": \"webpack --watch --mode development\",\n  \"prod\": \"webpack --mode production\",\n  \"test\": \"jest\"\n},\n","js","",[52,86,87,100,115,128,141,152],{"__ignoreMap":84},[88,89,92,96],"span",{"class":90,"line":91},"line",1,[88,93,95],{"class":94},"sWayO","\"scripts\"",[88,97,99],{"class":98},"s8XSl",": {\n",[88,101,103,106,109,112],{"class":90,"line":102},2,[88,104,105],{"class":94},"  \"server\"",[88,107,108],{"class":98},": ",[88,110,111],{"class":94},"\"webpack-dev-server --config webpack.config.js\"",[88,113,114],{"class":98},",\n",[88,116,118,121,123,126],{"class":90,"line":117},3,[88,119,120],{"class":94},"  \"dev\"",[88,122,108],{"class":98},[88,124,125],{"class":94},"\"webpack --watch --mode development\"",[88,127,114],{"class":98},[88,129,131,134,136,139],{"class":90,"line":130},4,[88,132,133],{"class":94},"  \"prod\"",[88,135,108],{"class":98},[88,137,138],{"class":94},"\"webpack --mode production\"",[88,140,114],{"class":98},[88,142,144,147,149],{"class":90,"line":143},5,[88,145,146],{"class":94},"  \"test\"",[88,148,108],{"class":98},[88,150,151],{"class":94},"\"jest\"\n",[88,153,155],{"class":90,"line":154},6,[88,156,157],{"class":98},"},\n",[17,159,160],{},[59,161],{"alt":162,"src":163},"scripts",